frameDefinitions: An Agent causes a Dryee (either a surface or an entire entity, inside and out) to become dry.
An Entity loses moisture with the outcome of being in a dry state.
An Item is in a state of dryness.
In this frame a Patient is in a phase brought about after a change of phase.
An Agent affects an Artifact so that it is no longer capable of performing its inherent function.
frameExamples: Collect up the  <t>thawed</t> water from the freezer section.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person performing the intentional act causing the <fen>Dryee</fen> to become dry.
The <fen>Dryee</fen> is the entity which has the water removed from it.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces the state of dryness. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Dryee</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Dryee</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> is the thing that loses moisture and becomes dry.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> becomes dry.
The <fen>Item</fen> exists in a state of dryness.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is the entity which has had its phase altered.
The sentient entity causes the Artifact to not function.
The device that no longer works.
An inanimate entity or force that renders the <fen>Artifact</fen> non-functional.
The time at which the event takes place.
The place at which the event takes place.
